FEEDBACK_DANGER_WARNING.text:
⚠️ SAFETY GAP DETECTED

Current Safety (S): {S}

By delaying your response, your safety margin has dropped. The situation is becoming harder to control.

FEEDBACK_RESOURCES_WARNING.text:
📉 RESOURCE DRAIN

Current Resources (R): {R}

Your rapid response has secured supplies, but at a significant cost. You are safer, but you have very little left to rely on.

FEEDBACK_SOCIAL_WARNING.text:
🤝 SOCIAL CAPITAL BOOST

Social Capital (SC): {SC}

You now have better information and stronger connections with people around you.

FEEDBACK_DANGER.text:
⚠️ CRITICAL VULNERABILITY

Safety (S): {S}

Your safety margin is low. You have not secured basic protection. The situation is becoming more dangerous as the storm approaches.

FEEDBACK_RESOURCES.text:
📉 RESOURCE DEPLETION

Resources (R): {R}

You have spent heavily to prepare. You are safer now, but your remaining resources are limited. This may make it harder to handle problems later.

FEEDBACK_EXHAUSTION.text:
😫 PHYSICAL STRAIN

Mobility (M): {M}

You are exhausted from the preparation. Your body is shaking. It may be harder to move quickly or react if the situation worsens.

FEEDBACK_RISK.text:
🚩 HIGH-RISK BEHAVIOR

High Risk Count: {HR}

You have taken actions that increase your risk. The situation is becoming harder to control, and your margin for error is shrinking.

FEEDBACK_FATAL_COASTAL.text:
⚠️ CATASTROPHIC IMPACT

Final Safety (S): {S}

The surge overwhelms your home. The force of the water leaves no time to react. Everything happens too quickly.

FEEDBACK_INJURY_COASTAL.text:
🚑 TRAUMA ALERT

Current Safety (S): {S}

You are alive, but the impact was severe. You are injured, and even simple movements feel difficult. The next phase will be harder.

FEEDBACK_EXHAUSTION_COASTAL.text:
🛑 PHYSICAL COLLAPSE

Current Mobility (M): {M}

You reached safety, but your strength is gone. You can barely move. Every action now feels heavy and slow.

FEEDBACK_RISK_COASTAL.text:
🚩 HIGH-RISK SITUATION

High Risk Count: {HR}

You stayed in a dangerous zone for too long. The situation became harder to control, and your margin for error is now very small.

FEEDBACK_FATAL_RIVER.text:
⚠️ CRITICAL FAILURE: SUBMERGED

Final Safety (S): {S}

The water rises too fast. The current pulls everything off balance. You lose control, and there is no time to recover.

FEEDBACK_ELECTROCUTION_RISK.text:
⚡ ELECTRICAL HAZARD

High Risk Count: {HR}

The water is now dangerous. Sparks flicker near outlets and wires. Every step feels uncertain, and one mistake could be fatal.

FEEDBACK_EXHAUSTION_RIVER.text:
🥶 EXHAUSTION

Current Mobility (M): {M}

The cold water drains your strength. Your body feels heavy, and each movement takes more effort than before. You are slowing down.

FEEDBACK_CONTAMINATION_ALERT.text:
☣️ CONTAMINATION RISK

Current Safety (S): {S}

The water is dirty and unsafe. You feel it on your skin and in your throat. Staying in it for too long will make things worse.

FEEDBACK_FATAL_HILL.text:
⚠️ BURIED

Final Safety (S): {S}

The ground gives way beneath you. Mud and debris rush down the slope. Everything happens at once, and there is no time to escape.

FEEDBACK_DIRECTION_ERROR.text:
🚩 WRONG MOVE

High Risk Count: {HR}

You run downhill. The ground becomes unstable beneath your feet. The slope moves faster than you can react.

FEEDBACK_MOBILITY_CRISIS.text:
😫 EXHAUSTION

Current Mobility (M): {M}

The mud is heavy and unstable. Your legs struggle to move. Each step takes more effort, and you begin to lose balance.

FEEDBACK_STRUCTURAL_FAILURE.text:
🏚️ UNSTABLE STRUCTURE

Current Safety (S): {S}

The house is still standing, but the ground beneath it is shifting. Cracks spread. Dust fills the air. The structure no longer feels safe.

FEEDBACK_POST_STORM_HAZARD.text:
🚑 SECONDARY DANGER

Current Safety (S): {S}

You leave the shelter. Outside, the ground is uneven and filled with debris. Loose wires hang low, and the water is still dirty. The danger has not passed.

FEEDBACK_SOCIAL_FRICTION.text:
📉 SOCIAL FRICTION

Social Capital (SC): {SC}

People around you begin to notice your actions. The atmosphere becomes tense. Others are less willing to help or share information with you.

FEEDBACK_CUMULATIVE_FATIGUE.text:
😫 EXHAUSTION

Current Mobility (M): {M}

You are drained. The heat, the noise, and the stress make it hard to rest. Your body feels heavy, and even small movements take effort.

FEEDBACK_TRUST_BUILDING.text:
🤝 TRUST

Social Capital (SC): {SC}

People begin to trust you. They share information and include you in decisions. You are no longer alone in this situation.

FEEDBACK_FATAL_ILLNESS.text:
⚠️ CRITICAL CONDITION

Final Safety (S): {S}

Your body begins to shut down. The water has made you sick. You feel weak, dizzy, and unable to stand. There is no help nearby.

FEEDBACK_PATHOGEN_EXPOSURE.text:
☣️ CONTAMINATION

High Risk Count: {HR}

You drink untreated water. It tastes wrong. Your stomach tightens. Something is not right, but you have no choice.

FEEDBACK_RESOURCE_BANKRUPTCY.text:
📉 LOW SUPPLIES

Current Resources (R): {R}

You have used up most of what you had. There is very little left. You are now relying on what others can provide.

FEEDBACK_PHYSICAL_LIMIT.text:
🛑 EXHAUSTION

Current Mobility (M): {M}

The heat and effort drain your strength. Your body feels heavy. Even standing takes effort. You cannot move easily anymore.
